最终最高预测准确率：~70%

    • 搭建pipline：
      1. 文件读取、解码与合并
      2. 引入batch处理
      3. 数据归一化
    • 搭建模型
      1. 搭建CNN模型，进行初步训练
      2. 查看预测成功率
    • 调优
      1. 调取预训练模型，并更换后续层类别，调整batch size
      2. 对图片进行翻转，增加到训练集中
      3. 改用GPU进行训练
    • 输出预测结果

Image recognition - Classifying 104 types of flowers using CNN¶

Final highest prediction accuracy: ~70%

  • Summary:

    • Build pipeline:
      1. File reading, decoding, and merging
      2. Batch processing
      3. Data normalization
    • Build the model:
      1. Construct a CNN model
      2. Check the accuracy rate
    • Optimization:
      1. Use a pre-trained model and modify the subsequent layers for fine-tuning
      2. Adjust the batch size
      3. Augment the training set by flip images
      4. Use GPU for training
    • Output prediction results

In [6]:
#method of extracting information from files
def parse_function(info):

    feature_description = {
        'id': tf.io.FixedLenFeature([], tf.string),
        'class': tf.io.FixedLenFeature([],tf.int64),
        'image': tf.io.FixedLenFeature([],tf.string),
    }

    parsed_info = tf.io.parse_single_example(info, feature_description)
    
    image = tf.io.decode_jpeg(parsed_info['image'], channels=3)
    

    return parsed_info['id'], parsed_info['class'], image
In [7]:
#method of extracting information from files
def parse_function_test(info):

    feature_description = {
        'id': tf.io.FixedLenFeature([], tf.string),
        'image': tf.io.FixedLenFeature([],tf.string),
    }

    parsed_info = tf.io.parse_single_example(info, feature_description)
    
    image = tf.io.decode_jpeg(parsed_info['image'], channels=3)
    

    return parsed_info['id'], image
In [8]:
#Method of extracting all files from one folder
def extract_from_folder(root_address, data_key):
    root_path = os.path.join(root_address, data_key)

    for index, file_name in enumerate(os.listdir(root_path)):
        final_path = os.path.join(root_path, file_name)
        #Extract
        if index == 0:
            dataset = tf.data.TFRecordDataset(final_path)
            parsed_dataset_all = dataset.map(parse_function)
        else:
            dataset = tf.data.TFRecordDataset(final_path)
            parsed_dataset = dataset.map(parse_function)
            parsed_dataset_all = parsed_dataset_all.concatenate(parsed_dataset)

    return parsed_dataset_all

#Scale
def divide_fn(feature1, feature2, feature3):
    feature3 = feature3 / 255
    return feature1, feature2, feature3

def divide_fn_test(feature1, feature2):
    feature2 = feature2 / 255
    return feature1, feature2
In [14]:

scaled_val_192 = val_192.map(lambda f1, f2, f3: divide_fn(f1, f2, f3))
scaled_test_192 = test_192.map(lambda f1, f2: divide_fn_test(f1, f2))

Build a CNN model using a pretrained model¶

In [15]:
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Conv2D, GlobalAveragePooling2D, Dense, Flatten
In [16]:
pretrained_model_192 = tf.keras.applications.vgg16.VGG16(
    weights = 'imagenet',
    include_top = False,
    input_shape = [192, 192, 3]
)
pretrained_model_192.trainable = False

model_192 = tf.keras.Sequential([
    pretrained_model_192,
    GlobalAveragePooling2D(),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(104, activation='softmax')
    
])

model_192.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss=tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(),
              metrics=['sparse_categorical_accuracy'])
